<HEADLINE>Boat grounded</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>5</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975060998</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A fishing boat with six crewmen on board which ran aground on a sandbank early
yesterday at the approach to Montrose harbour was later towed clear, Aberdeen
Coastguard said.
The 86ft Peterhead-registered Sustain got into difficulties at about 6am. The
Montrose lifeboat stood buy until the afternoon's high tide when the vessel was
successfully towed off and later docked.
</TEXT>
