<DOCID>GH951204-000006</DOCID>
<DATE>951204</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Bobbitt revenge by jealous wife</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975060999</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Manila
A JEALOUS Filipina wife severed her husband's penis while he slept after she
learned he was having an affair with another woman.
Sales agent Ernesto Redito, 45, felt pain in his groin when he awoke on Friday
in his house in Plaridel town and screamed when he saw his sex organ had been
cut off, reported the newspaper Tempo. ``I could not stand his philandering any
more,'' Redito's wife Eva told police.
She finally decided to do something on learning the other woman was pregnant,
the paper said.
Doctors at the hospital where Redito was taken were still considering whether
the severed organ could be re-attached. The report did not say if Redito would
press charges.
The incident was the latest of several cases of Filipinas cutting their
husband's penises to be reported since last year's case involving US manicurist
Lorena Bobbitt, who severed her husband's organ in retaliation for sexual
assaults.
q The Philippines has filed a Bill banning morticians from hospitals. MP
Reynaldo Calalay denounced as ``vultures'' the agents of funeral parlours who
sit around waiting for news of a death.-Reuter.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
