<DATE>951204</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Against dress uniformity</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>12</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975061009</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE only reason I dislike having to go to my building society office - apart
from the queue and my diminishing bank balance - is that I have to look at all
these pleasant efficient ladies looking like clones in their identikit
uniforms. Ugh!
What powers these employers have and exert - why? Presumably they think their
investors like to see dress uniformity. As far as I am concerned they are most
definitely wrong.
I wonder why they bother to put first names at the windows. With these
dress-alikes surely numbers would be more appropriate.
Margaret C Duncan,
37 Credon Drive,
Airdrie.
</TEXT>
