<HEADLINE>Police trace escapee Moore</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<FLAG>news digest</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975061012</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Police trace
escapee Moore
ESCAPED psychiatric patient Robert Moore was last night back in custody after
being traced by police to Manchester. A nationwide search was launched after
Moore, 52, went missing from Dykebar Hospital in Paisley on Thursday night.
In 1971 he was acquitted of murder on the grounds of insanity and committed to
hospital without limit of time. The Scottish Office warned that while his
recent behaviour did not cause significant concern Moore could be a danger in
certain circumstances. He was transferred to Dykebar from the State Hospital at
Carstairs in 1993.
Rape charge
A MAN is due to appear in court at Dunoon today, charged with raping a
14-year-old girl. Mr Daniel Connel Bonnar, 26, of Shore Road, Blairmore, is
also charged with attempted house-breaking.
Wind power plan
THE English electricity generating company, Powergen, has asked Argyll and Bute
District Council for permission to investigate the viability of wind power on
Mull. It wants to erect a 30-metre-high meteorological mast at Dervaig.
Council renamed
DUMBARTON and Clydebank Council, which takes control of both towns on April 1,
is to be re-named West Dunbartonshire Council. This follows a plea to schools
and community groups for suggestions.
Ostrich victim
ARCHITECT David Smith, who gave up his day job to set up an ostrich farm, faces
three months on the sick list after one of the 30-stone birds he was unloading
from a lorry at Virginia Water, Surrey, crushed him in a stampede and another
broke his leg.
Disabled day
A TORCHLIT procession in the Royal Mile yesterday marked United Nations
International Day for People with Disabilities, as well as signalling the end
of a week of events for disabled people, organised by Edinburgh District
Council.
#10.6m jackpot
A SINGLE ticket scooped the #10,613,401 jackpot in Saturday's National Lottery.
Thirty-five winners with five correct numbers and the bonus ball will each get
#93,304, and 693 tickets with five numbers win #2945. Four numbers correct
means #100 each. The numbers were 15, 16, 19, 26, 35 and 46, with 7 as the
bonus ball. Camelot estimated that #24,958,204 would be donated to good causes.
</TEXT>
