<TEXT>
I FIND it incredible that Alexander Linklater can review (November 25) a
biography of the writer and political philosopher, Raymond Williams, without
once mentioning his forcefully expressed commitment to Welsh national freedom.
Neil R MacCallum,
18 Redford Avenue,
Edinburgh.
