<DOCNO>GH951204-000035</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951204-000035</DOCID>
<DATE>951204</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Forte sells Lillywhites sport shops for #28m</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>15</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975061028</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
HOTEL giant Forte, which is under #3400m bid siege by Granada, has sold its
Lillywhites sports chain for #28.5m.
Granada, whose interests span broadcasting to motorway service stations,
announced when it launched its hostile offer last month that it would sell
Lillywhites if the bid succeeded.
Lillywhites, with its flagship store in central London, recently opened a
second branch in the Lakeside shopping centre in Thurrock, Essex. It also has
outlets in St Andrews and Gatwick.
The sale to Jeronimo Martins, a Portuguese retailing group, is likely to form a
key part of Forte's defence strategy. The group, which is due to post its
defence document to shareholders over the next few days, is thought likely to
highlight the Lillywhites sale as demonstrating its ability to unlock hidden
value from its businesses. The price raised by the sale is more than twice the
#12m value in the group's accounts.
</TEXT>
