Mars rock sold
NEW YORK: Two meteorites from Mars were the star performers at the world's
second auction of natural history items. The larger of two pieces of Martian
meteorite was sold for nearly #5000, more than three times its pre-sale
estimate, and the smaller for #1763, nearly seven times its estimate.
Safety last
AVEZZANO: An Italian man who had a heart condition collapsed and died after
being made to pass repeatedly through a supermarket security device. Gio Maria
Baruffa, a 71-year-old retired police officer, collapsed as he was accompanying
a store manager into a back office and died later in hospital.
