Warden injured
AN animal warden at Knowsley Safari Park, Merseyside, Mr William Middleton, 36,
is seriously ill in hospital with spinal and head injuries after being crushed
by the 12ft sliding gates of an elephant house yesterday.
Lottery cash
for swimmers
FUNDRAISERS in Kirkcudbright are celebrating after they were told of a #253,000
National Lottery grant for the town's swimming pool project.
The Kirkcudbright Swimming Pool Company now has #730,000 in cash and promises
of grants. It plans to have a sod-cutting ceremony on May 1, with the pool at
Castledykes completed in about six months.
Storm practice
THE south-easterly storm yesterday brought power cuts and cancelled ferries to
Shetland, but Lerwick lifeboat went out in the teeth of the gale for an hour,
for lifeboat men to practise.
