q GLASGOW officials were clearly unhappy last night after disenchanted centre
Chris Simmers defected to Edinburgh - just three days before the start of the
District Championship.
Simmers made the sudden switch after having been relegated to the Glasgow bench
to make way for Test player Ian Jardine to come into the side to face North and
Midlands at Kirkcaldy on Wednesday.
Ironically, Jardine is doubtful with a neck injury and   Simmers - who played
well in last month's victory over South African tourists Griqualand West -
would probably have played.
Glasgow still have to name a replacement.
q CARDIFF suffered their second successive home defeat in the Heineken League
first division on Saturday, Bridgend completing a double over the league
leaders with a 19-18 triumph.
Pontypridd closed the gap at the top by beating Ebbw Vale.
