<TEXT>
JUNIORS
MOST of the junior ``big guns'' made it through to the fourth round of the OVD
Cup following Saturday's ties. Two clubs, however, who will have to overcome
replays this week are last season's finalists, Camelon and Whitburn.
Holders Camelon travelled to meet Ayrshire second-division side Darvel and
could manage only a 3-3 draw despite Darvel being reduced to 10 men early in
the first half.
Geoff Strachan put Arbroath 1-0 ahead in the sixth minute of their game against
Whitburn with ``Oscar'' Taylor equalising with a penalty by half-time.
Largs Thistle bounced back from last week's 7-0 defeat by Auchinleck to trounce
Muirkirk 5-0 and a Milton Thompson double helped Irvine Meadow to a fine 4-1
win over Dundee Violet. Inverurie Loco Works came from behind to earn a replay
against Kilbirnie Ladeside.
A depleted Cumnock team welcomed back long-term injury victim Paul Anderson for
their all-Ayrshire tie against Beith.
Cumnock went ahead in 15 minutes when Jim McCann of Beith turned a Norman
Montgomery shot into his own net. In another setback for Beith, Peter McKenna
was stretchered off before half-time.
An Ian Dick goal in the first minute of the second half set Cumnock on their
way to a comprehensive win. Two more goals from Dick to complete his hat trick
and one from Chris Wilson gave Cumnock a 5-1 victory.
Home advantage proved decisive in Kilwinning's 1-0 victory over Kelty Hearts.
Skipper Danny Sloan, making his comeback after a lengthy suspension, scored on
the hour.
A goal either side of half-time by Darren Stewart and Paul McLean took Pollok
through against 10-man Craigmark Burntonians.
Carluke Rovers lost ex-Airdrie striker Ross Donaldson with a leg break after he
had scored a double to give them a 3-3 draw with Rosyth.
Leading 1-0 with three minutes to go, Larkhall Thistle looked set for the
fourth round. However, two late goals by Livingston's veteran striker Tom Ward
took the new town club into the next round.
Tayport could manage only a draw against a nine-man Baillieston team who had
taken the lead in 16 minutes with a Nicholson goal. Hamish McKay equalised for
Tayport in 68 minutes.
Blantyre Vics increased their lead at the top of the Reebok First Division with
a 3-0 win over Vale of Clyde.
In midweek, the junior association fined Kinloss FC #200 and banned them from
the OVD Cup for the next two seasons for failing to play their second-round
game against Dundee St Joseph's.
The draw for the fourth round of the OVD Cup, with ties due to be played on
January 20, will take place in Kilbirnie's Garnock Labour Club next Sunday
afternoon. Results:
