<TEXT>
NORTH and Midlands had almost all the pressure in their Under-18 inter-district
championship match with the South at Kinloss on Saturday.
Only numerous, basic mistakes of dropped and forward passes by the North and
Midlands side saved the South from receiving a hefty defeat.
Another factor in this low scoring match was the failure of Graham Kiddie to
land his many kicks at goal.
The home side were 15-0 up at the interval from tries by Ross Chassels and
Jamie Philip (both Aberdeen University), and Alan Davidson (Morgan Academy).
Following the break, South lifted their play and flanker Ian McDougall (Kelso
Harlequins) crashed over for an unconverted try. In the closing quarter of the
match, the North and Midlands added their fourth unconverted try of the match
when Jonathan Davies (Howe of Fife) went over.
Dan McDonald, the Huntly right-wing, broke a bone in a hand, and was replaced
by Dave Jones of Dunferm-line/Rosyth.
