<TEXT>
HIGHLAND LEAGUE
FORT William could hold on to five top players put up for free transfer at the
weekend because of a cash shortage.
A mystery benefactor is understood to have offered to meet the Inverness and
Aberdeen-based quintet's travelling expenses.
Defenders Mike Andrew and Billy Skinner, goalkeeper Billy Neilson, midfielder
Alan MacDonald, and top scorer Alan Moir, will now be offered the chance to
stay.
Fort manager Henrik Madej said: ``It has been a traumatic week for me. They are
not only good footballers, but good personal friends. ''
Enquiries have been made about the five, but Madej stressed: ``They are all
still signed to Fort William and, unless any are set on leaving, they will
remain so.''
All five thought they were lining up for Fort for the last time on Saturday,
and the air of gloom showed as Deveronvale destroyed the visitors 4-1.
Elsewhere, Keith gained revenge for their Qualifying Cup final defeat by
beating Fraserburgh 4-2 with Scott Taylor scoring a double.
Peterhead lost 2-1 at home to Brora, and Elgin were trounced 4-1 at Buckie.
Cove Rangers secured a convincing 4-1 win against Nairn County.
</TEXT>
