<TEXT>
RALLYING
YESTERDAY'S South West Saab Galloway Hills event brought the Scottish forest
rallying season to its traditional close for the year, and it was the Irish who
carried off the spoils of victory.
Stephen Harron and Avril Magee won by almost a minute at the end of 40 miles of
forest stages. Harron had only recently discovered his winning ways when he
took his first event two months ago at Enniskillen, and he carried that form
across the water yesterday.
He contested this event for the first time last year when he had been second
overall until his gearbox broke, but there was no stopping him yesterday. He
took 16 seconds out of the 66 car field on the first of five stages and
thereafter pulled away.
Sandy Dalgarno salvaged Scottish pride with second place. Third was Jon Burn,
fresh from victory on the previous day's Grizedale Stages in the Lake District.
Four-times Scottish champion Drew Gallacher finished fourth overall, following
on from his runner-up position behind Burn in England the previous day. Final
results:
1, Stephen Harron/Avril Magee (Ford Sierra Cosworth) 41min 55sec; 2, Sandy
Dalgarno/Sandy Taylor (Ford Escort Cosworth) 42-46; 3, Jon Burn/Stan Quirk
(Ford Sierra Cosworth) 42-58; 4, Drew Gallacher/Phil Sandham (Ford Escort
Cosworth) 43-39; 5, George Gauld/Roy Campbell (Ford Escort Cosworth) 43-57; 6,
Mike Stephenson/Roy Jarvis (Ford Escort Cosworth) 44-20; 7, Jock Armstrong/John
Richardson (Peugeot 205) 45-03; 8, Alan Dickson/Graham Bisset (Ford Escort
Cosworth) 45-05; 9, Richard Montgomery/Greg Brownlow (Ford Sierra Cosworth)
45-25; 10, Derek Crossan/Peter Dowds (Opel Manta) 45-37.
