<HEADLINE>Judo Scots in golden show</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<FLAG>sport</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975061105</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SCOTS captured 10 medals, including four golds, in the British Championships in
Bangor, Northern Ireland, at the weekend.
John Buchanan (under-60 kilos), Paul Leishman (under-71k), and Gary Edwards
(under-86k) all took senior titles, with David Sommerville (under-71k) picking
up a silver and Jonathan Gavin (under-78k) a bronze.
Jenny Bryan (under-56k) also struck silver, but Kirsti Weir could manage only a
bronze in defence of her under-61k title. Fiona Robertson (under-48k) also
struck bronze.
There was more success for the Scots in yesterday's junior championships, with
Hamilton's John Goldie winning the under-78k title and Susie Crawford taking
silver in the under-52k class.
</TEXT>
