<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH951204-000113</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951204-000113</DOCID>
<DATE>951204</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Cash lures Jardel to Ibrox</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>IAN BROADLEY</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>1</PAGE>
<FLAG>sport</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975061106</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BRAZILIAN star Jardel has revealed that money was the main consideration in
deciding his future lies with Rangers.
The striker was responding to criticism on Dutch television from Ajax captain
Danny Blind, who maintained that furthering Jardel's career with a bigger club
should have been the first priority.
Blind, whose penalty kick defeated Gremio to bring the World Club Championship
to Ajax, insisted: ``Jardel is a very good player and certainly could find a
place with Ajax. Everyone saw his qualities in the final.
``It is a shame he chooses to join a physical team like Rangers and puts money
before football. If you concentrate on improve your ability, then money will
come later. Most of our players could now sign for any club in Europe.''
Jardel, who will cost Rangers #2.5m to buy from the South American champions,
admitted: ``No other club offered as much money as Rangers. The salary is much
bigger than I imagined I would earn.
``I do not know very much about Scottish football except that it will be cold
and wet. But when you are to be paid such a wage there is no point in moaning.
``I will be expected to perform and produce the goods, just like I did in
Brazil, where I attracted the interest of many clubs.
``Many people were surprised when Romario and then Ronaldo, two of Brazil's
best players, left for a small country like Holland to join PSV Eindhoven. The
conditions there are the same as Scotland.
``They could have chosen the glamour of Serie A, Spain or stayed in Brazil but
they became rich, famous, and better players in Holland. Romario then moved on
to a bigger stage with Barcelona and Ronaldo will follow. I can do the same
with Rangers.
``I don't have to spend the rest of my career in Scotland but while I am there
I will make sure the club and their supporters are satisfied with my
performances.''
</TEXT>
