<HEADLINE>Win for promoted Currie helps light up Malleny Park</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<FLAG>sport</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975061108</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
CURRIE eventually ran out winners against an experimental Edinburgh line-up in
an entertaining game to mark the opening of the new #45,000 floodlights at
Malleny Park.
Currie were first to score in just five minutes, when Dougie Rogerson and
Michael Plumb sent New Zealander Dean Sheppard cutting inside the defence to
score between the posts, John Morrison converting.
It was Sheppard again who crossed for a try on the half-hour but Campbell
Aitken opened Edinburgh's account with a penalty four minutes before half-time,
and the gap was narrowed further thanks to a fine try from Biggar centre
Lindsay Graham, converted by Michael Duncan.
Scott Forrester scored a try for Currie in 54 minutes but, with both teams keen
to play an expansive game, Edinburgh took the lead with a Duncan penalty and a
try in 61 minutes from Heriot's full back Stewart Lang.
Currie finished the stronger side, and with six minutes remaining, No.8 Mark
Blair broke away from a scrummage and sent in Rogerson for a touchdown, then
Forrester scored his second with the last move of the game, both converted by
Morrison.
The match proved costly in terms of injuries for Edinburgh, and for Heriot's in
particular. Graham Dall retired with a broken tooth while Tam McVie was
stretchered off and taken to hospital for a check-up, and Campbell Aitken
departed at half-time.
A substantially different Edinburgh team will begin their inter-district
championship challenge against the Exiles on Wednesday.
Currie - D Sheppard; G Keen, M Plumb, D Wilson, S Forrester; J Morrison, D
Rogerson; N McIlroy, K Barrie (both Jed-Forrest), P Calder, C Eagle, G
Hamilton, F Thompson, M Blair and S Logan. Replacement - I Russell for Thomson
(63min).
Edinburgh - S Lang (Heriot's); C Robertson (Currie), C Murray (Edinburgh
Accies), L Graham (Biggar), C Aitken (Heriot's); M Duncan (Edinburgh Accies); G
Burns, R McNulty and A Cadzow (all Stewart's Melville), S Paul (Heriot's), M
McVie and S Murray (both Edinburgh Accies), T McVie (Heriot's), D Clark
(Stewart's Melville), G Dall (Heriot's). Replacements - F McMillan (Heriot's)
for Aitken (41); M Livingstone (Heriot's) for McVie (21); N Penny (Stewart's
Melville) for Dall (13).
Referee - R Megson (Edinburgh Wanderers).
SCORERS: Currie - Sheppard, 2t; Forrester, 2t; Rogerson, 1t; Morrison 3c.
Edinburgh - Graham, 1t; Lang, 1t; Aitken, 1p; Duncan, 1p, 1c.
Currie 31, Edinburgh 18
</TEXT>
