<TEXT>
MEN'S HOCKEY
CIBA Kelburne and Insights Inverleith will not figure this season in the battle
for the First Division title in the National Indoor league.
Instead they have been doomed to the relegation playoffs after occupying the
bottom two positions at the end of the first phase.
Their miserable form was matched only yesterday by the Scottish Hockey Union's
organisation of the day's event when the technical delegate and one of the
umpires failed to appear at the Bells sports centre in Perth.
A more pleasing aspect of the day's play was Grange giving the distinct
impression that they could emerge as potential rivals to Insights Menzieshill
and MIM, despite losing 7-1 yesterday to Menzieshill.
MIM too are gradually moving into their old familiar groove. Like Menzieshill
they picked up maximum points.
In Division Two Morgan catapulted themselves up the table by crushing Aberdeen
side Stronachs AGSFP 17-6.
JOSEPH DILLON
