<HEADLINE>Scots rocked by Robertson</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>JOSEPH DILLON</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>5</PAGE>
<FLAG>sport</FLAG>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>975061117</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
PAULINE Robertson, the Scottish captain, has dropped a bombshell on the sport
by announcing her withdrawal from the squad for the finals of the European
Indoor Nations Cup, which Scotland will be hosting at Glasgow's Kelvin Hall
from January 26 to 28.
Robertson, who also is the vice-captain of the Great Britain squad, yesterday
gave ``heavy work commitments'' as one of the reasons behind her decision, but
also pointed out ``with Great Britain now through to the Olympic Games in
Atlanta, this is going to be the most important year in my career and I want to
concentrate on the Olympics.''
Edinburgh Ladies, for whom Robertson plays indoors, will also be without her
services for the European Club Championship finals in Bratislavia.
The Edinburgh club won all their three games at the Bells Sports Centre in
Perth on Saturday, but it was Western Klick Photopoint, playing the better
hockey on the day, who richly deserved to top the table after the first session
on goal difference.
WOMEN'S HOCKEY
