BOWLING
PRESTWICK'S David Gourlay Jr, who already holds the record of eight national
indoor titles, is just two games away from increasing that total to nine after
having come through from the Ardrossan area play-downs in the CIS Insurance
National Indoor Fours championship.
Gourlay guided his rink, containing brother Ian at lead, Stuart Reid, and Edric
Vorsterman through to the semi-finals at the West of Scotland stadium next
month, when they beat Ian Cowan's Paisley rink 22-13.
Paisley earlier had defeated defending champions Blantyre 22-15 in the second
round. Also through to the semi-finals are world indoors pairs champion Alex
Marshall's Bainfield rink, Graham Robertson's East Lothian side, and the rink
from Cowal skipped by Ian McIntyre.
The Bainfield rink got there with a 20-10 win over John Scott's Edinburgh side,
while East Lothian clinched their last four slot when they beat Perth 22-16 at
