<TEXT>
JOHN Corson returned refreshed from a two-week lay-off to collect the fifth
consecutive victory for his J35 Salamander XII yesterday off Inverkip as the
Scottish Islands Liqueur Frostbite Series ended, writes Andi Robertson.
With eight wins and a second place over the two late-season series, the
Salamander crew yesterday collected the Kip Marina Trophy for the best
performance of all four classes.
Although the breeze faltered Corson's crew stayed on top and had a two-minute
margin over Malcolm Wootton's Tripp 36 Sweet Thing.
Scott Chalmers' Beneteau First Class 10 Highlander took fourth, but had already
won Class 2.
Martin Maiden's Itch returned to winning form at just the right time to win
Class 3. Ian Rice's modified Intro Screwball won the fourth division by 5.75
points. Results:
Class 1, final race - 1, Salamander XII, J Corson; 2, Sweet Thing, M Wootton;
3, Looney Tunes, I Cameron. Overall - 1, Salamander XII, 3.0pts; 2, Sweet
Thing, 9; 3, Looney Tunes, 11. Class 2, final race - 1, Oskar II, D Hanley; 2,
Night Moth, M Maclaurin; 3, T'Jig, J Dryburgh. Overall - 1, Highlander, S
Chalmers, 6.5; 2, Oskar II, 9.7; 3, T'Jig, 9.75. Class 3 final race - 1, Itch,
M Maiden; 2, Carmen, P Scutt; 3, Panache, N Wilson. Overall - 1, Itch, 6.25; 2,
Makin Waves, 6.5; 3, Carmen, 9. Class 4 final race - 1, Screwball, I Rice; 2,
Upstart, Ritchie &amp; Black; 3, Introuvable, P Cooper. Overall - 1, Screwball,
3.0; 2, Upstart 8.75; 3, Introuvable,20.
