<HEADLINE>Youth had its day</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<FLAG>sport</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975061142</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BILL Sutherland may be correct in stating that 15-year-old Sean Christie of
Forfar Athletic is younger than was Ronnie Simpson when he kept goal for
Queen's Park in 1946.
Ronnie Simpson, however, played for Queen's Park in 1945 when he was 14. His
first match was a 5-2 victory against Clyde in the Summer Cup. In the second
round, Bobby Brown kept goal in a 1-0 defeat at Greenock. Simpson came in again
for the second leg at Hampden, which was scoreless.
David C Miller,
80 Prestonfield,
Milngavie.
</TEXT>
