<HEADLINE>Tribute to BBC radio producer</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Obituary</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975061144</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TRIBUTE was paid yesterday to BBC producer Mr Geoffrey Cameron, who died at the
weekend aged 54.
Mr Cameron was a reporter with the corporation in the early 1960s and went on
to produce Good Morning Scotland. He was head of current affairs at Radio
Scotland in the 1980s and launched its Newsweek and Eye to Eye current affairs
programmes. Over the last year he was an independent producer for the BBC.
BBC Scotland controller John McCormick said he was           a great journalist
and programme-maker.
Mr Cameron leaves a wife, two daughters and a son.
</TEXT>
